gomodel:SYNGO_1693  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: In figures 4, 5, and 7 the authors use immunogold electron microscopy to localize CALM in rat synapses. Figure 4 is synapses from CA1 neurone and figure 5 is synapses from cerebellar granule cells on Purkinje neurons. Figure 7 also uses the granule cell synapses. The immunogold labelling localizes to the pre synapse and figure 7 shows a pool on clathrin-coated vesicles.\n\n6/12/2017 Pim\n- The localization to the presynaptic endocytic zone is inferred from the following information:\n1. PICALM has a well established role in clathrin coat assembly during endocytosis in non-neuronal system.\n2. Next to the active zone is a (stucturally poorly defined) hotspot of SV endocytosis names the 'presynaptic endocytic zone'. Fig.4K hows localization of PICALM to a corresponding region bordering the AZ.\n3. Localization among clathrin-coated SV is observed (Fig.4C,D,...)\n\nThese data suggest that (at least in part of its function lifecycle) PICALM is localized to the presynaptic endocytic zone membrane.. Experimental description: From results, \"Two rats were processed for postembedding immunogold labelling...\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7806-5662" ;
        dc:date           "2017-12-15" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_1693" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

